Now, why should you care about this?

00:00:50.730 --> 00:00:54.449
Because my friend, being
proficient in computer aptitude

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:56.339
is vital in today's world.

00:00:56.879 --> 00:01:01.559
Understanding these abbreviations helps
you communicate clearly whether you

00:01:01.559 --> 00:01:06.660
are discussing digital systems, network
problems, or even cybersecurity stuff.

00:01:07.080 --> 00:01:11.695
It basically enables everyone to
work efficiently and solve problems

00:01:11.765 --> 00:01:13.655
without getting lost in translation.

00:01:15.195 --> 00:01:19.875
Breakdown of question types based on
the typical patterns in your exam.

00:01:20.054 --> 00:01:23.265
Questions on this topic
usually come in two flavors.

00:01:23.625 --> 00:01:29.354
First, and this is the most common one
with about an 80% frequency, is asking

00:01:29.354 --> 00:01:31.395
for the full form of an abbreviation.

00:01:31.774 --> 00:01:36.695
They'll give you a short form, say
CPU, and ask you to pick its complete

00:01:36.755 --> 00:01:38.794
expanded name from the options.

00:01:39.274 --> 00:01:44.285
The second type, which you'll see about
20% of the time, is the complete opposite.

00:01:44.675 --> 00:01:49.024
They'll give you the full form,
like worldwide web and ask for its

00:01:49.024 --> 00:01:51.725
correct abbreviation, formulas, and.

00:01:52.835 --> 00:01:57.035
Now, there are no magic formulas
for remembering these, but I do

00:01:57.035 --> 00:01:58.715
have some clever tricks for you.

00:01:59.285 --> 00:02:01.145
First is categorization.

00:02:01.655 --> 00:02:05.885
Try grouping the abbreviations by
their category, like putting all

00:02:05.885 --> 00:02:10.384
hardware ones together, all software
ones in another list, and so on.

00:02:10.895 --> 00:02:12.560
It helps to organize your brain.

00:02:13.299 --> 00:02:16.989
Next, the good old flashcards
method is fantastic.

00:02:17.410 --> 00:02:21.310
Write the abbreviation on one side
and the full form on the other.

00:02:21.760 --> 00:02:25.780
You can also create mnemonics,
which are memorable little phrases

00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:29.890
where the first letter of each word
helps you remember the abbreviation.

00:02:30.340 --> 00:02:33.760
Of course, regular revision
is the key to success.

00:02:34.149 --> 00:02:37.840
You must review a few
abbreviations daily or weekly.

00:02:38.260 --> 00:02:40.930
Finally, try some contextual learning.

00:02:41.335 --> 00:02:45.234
If you understand what the full
term actually means, remembering its

00:02:45.234 --> 00:02:46.825
short form becomes a piece of cake.

00:02:48.285 --> 00:02:49.695
Methods of solving.

00:02:50.204 --> 00:02:53.204
When you see a question on
abbreviations, here is a

00:02:53.204 --> 00:02:55.275
step-by-step method to tackle it.

00:02:55.695 --> 00:02:59.505
First and most importantly,
read the question carefully.

00:02:59.924 --> 00:03:04.274
You need to be sure if they're asking
for the full form or the abbreviation.

00:03:04.710 --> 00:03:08.910
Next, try to recall the full form
abbreviation from your memory.

00:03:09.390 --> 00:03:14.160
Then analyze the options provided,
look at them closely and start

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:16.200
to eliminate incorrect options.

00:03:16.590 --> 00:03:20.490
Many times the wrong options will
have one or two correct words,

00:03:20.670 --> 00:03:22.019
but will be wrong over overall.

00:03:22.550 --> 00:03:24.590
They are just there to confuse you.

00:03:25.100 --> 00:03:29.060
After you've cleared out the rubbish,
you can select the best fit, which

00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:33.140
will be the option that most accurately
represents the correct answer,

00:03:33.440 --> 00:03:35.540
shortcuts and smart techniques.

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:39.110
Looking for some smart
techniques, I've got you covered.

00:03:39.680 --> 00:03:43.730
A good trick is to focus on
common prefixes, suffixes.

00:03:44.304 --> 00:03:50.635
Many abbreviations share parts like inter
for internet or OS for operating system.

00:03:51.024 --> 00:03:54.054
Recognizing these patterns
is a great shortcut.

00:03:54.625 --> 00:03:57.144
Another simple trick is to sound it out.

00:03:57.595 --> 00:04:01.404
Sometimes just saying the
abbreviation out loud can trigger

00:04:01.404 --> 00:04:02.660
your memory of the full name.

00:04:03.440 --> 00:04:08.030
You can also use Visual Association
by linking the abbreviation

00:04:08.030 --> 00:04:12.680
to an image or a concept that
relates to its meaning, my friend.

00:04:12.830 --> 00:04:15.500
You must also practice with mock tests.

00:04:15.890 --> 00:04:20.270
This is the best way to get faster
and more confident for the exam day.

00:04:20.840 --> 00:04:25.280
And a pro tip, prioritize
high frequency abbreviations.

00:04:25.610 --> 00:04:29.420
Focus on memorizing the most
common ones first as they have

00:04:29.420 --> 00:04:30.530
a higher chance of showing up.

00:04:32.114 --> 00:04:34.335
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:04:34.724 --> 00:04:38.205
Now let's talk about the
common traps people fall into.

00:04:38.594 --> 00:04:42.945
The biggest one is mixing up
similar abbreviations like confusing

00:04:42.945 --> 00:04:45.854
Lan with Van or Ram with rom.

00:04:46.184 --> 00:04:48.554
Be very careful with these lookalikes.

00:04:48.930 --> 00:04:52.320
Another silly mistake is getting
the incorrect word order.

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:57.090
You might remember all the right words,
but put them in the wrong sequence.

00:04:57.420 --> 00:05:01.830
For example, the full form of
DOS is disc operating system,

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:04.110
not operating system disc.

00:05:04.620 --> 00:05:07.890
Also watch out for
ignoring case sensitivity.

00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:12.905
While not always tested strictly,
some abbreviations like HTML

00:05:13.085 --> 00:05:14.465
are standard in uppercase.

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:19.760
Don't go about adding omitting words from
the full form, just because it sounds

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:25.369
right, and the biggest mistake of all
is relying solely on rote memorization.

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:29.719
If you don't understand the concept,
you'll forget it very quickly.

